text: Symphony No. 39 is a symphony written by Joseph Haydn. It was written in 1765. It is written in the Sturm und Drang style. == Music == The symphony is written for two oboes, four horns, and strings. It has four movements: #Allegro assai, #Andante, in E major #Menuet & Trio, #Finale: Allegro di molto, == References == Symphony 039 Category:1765 works Category:Compositions in G minor
title: Symphony No. 39 (Haydn)
